# Akira Pentest Skills

When the user is working on security testing, bug bounty, penetration testing, or CTF challenges,
use the relevant Akira skill by reading and following the instructions in the skill file.

## Skill Map

| User asks about | Read and follow |
|---|---|
| Starting a pentest, new target, scope | `skills/plan-engagement/SKILL.md` |
| Recon, subdomains, live hosts, phase 1 | `skills/recon/SKILL.md` |
| Secrets, API keys, tokens, phase 2 | `skills/secrets/SKILL.md` |
| XSS, SQLi, nuclei, exploitation, phase 3 | `skills/exploit/SKILL.md` |
| Zero-days, chain attacks, JWT, WAF bypass | `skills/zerodayhunt/SKILL.md` |
| Aggregating findings, triage, severity | `skills/triage/SKILL.md` |
| Writing report, generating report | `skills/report/SKILL.md` |
| Active Directory, BloodHound, Kerberoast | `skills/ad-attacks/SKILL.md` |
| OAuth, OIDC, SSO, account takeover | `skills/oauth-attacks/SKILL.md` |
| Race conditions, double-spend, TOCTOU | `skills/race-conditions/SKILL.md` |
| AWS, GCP, Azure, Kubernetes | `skills/cloud-audit/SKILL.md` |
| CTF, HackTheBox, TryHackMe, pwn | `skills/ctf/SKILL.md` |

## Phase Order

```
plan-engagement -> recon -> secrets -> exploit -> zerodayhunt -> triage -> report
```

## Evidence Rule

Never claim a finding without quoting the exact HTTP response proving it.
Empty body or WAF-intercepted response is not evidence of a vulnerability.

## Authorization

Only on authorized targets: bug bounty programs, authorized pentests, CTF competitions.
